136 (L)\n|Malaysia XI\n|-\n|3.\n|30 July 2012\n|National Stadium, Bukit Jalil\n| K. Rajagopal\n| [[Manchester City F.C|Manchester City]]\n|1\u20133 (L)\n|Malaysia XI\n|-\n|}\n\n==Personal life==\nKhairul Fahmi is the fourth of five siblings. He received his early education at the Sekolah Kebangsaan Tapang, Kota Bharu. Then he entered Sekolah Sukan Bandar Penawar, Johor Bahru. After that he furthered [[Bukit Jalil Sports School]] (National Sports School). He was active in sports and has represented the school since primary school. On 28 December 2012, Khairul Fahmi married Nur Eilunie Natasha Jaafar.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.infoharian.com/foto-kahwin-khairul-fahmi-dan-leuniey.html|title=Gambar Kahwin Khairul Fahmi Apek Dan Leuniey|date=28 December 2012|website=InfoHarian|publisher=infoharian.com|language=Malay|access-date=24 June 2016}}</ref> They have a daughter named Kayla Elayna, and a son named Khaleel Emir.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mynewshub.my/myartis/?p=3378|title=Gambar Comel Anak Khairul Fahmi Dan Leuniey|date=10 February 2014|website=MyNewsHub.my|language=Malay|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140429045129/http://mynewshub.my/myartis/?p=3378|archive-date=29 April 2014|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n\n===Clubs===\n'''Kelantan'''\n* [[Malaysia Cup]] (2): [[2010 Malaysia Cup|2010]], [[2012 Malaysia Cup|2012]]\n* [[Piala Sumbangsih|Malaysia Charity Shield]] (1): 2011\n* [[Malaysia Super League]] (2): [[2011 Malaysia Super League|2011]], [[2012 Malaysia Super League|2012]]\n* [[Malaysia FA Cup]] (2): [[2012 Malaysia FA Cup|2012]], [[2013 Malaysia FA Cup|2013]] Runner-up [[2015 Malaysia FA Cup|2015]]\n\n===International===\n* [[AFF Suzuki Cup]]:\n::Winners: [[2010 AFF Suzuki Cup|2010]]\n::Runner Up: [[2014 AFF Suzuki Cup|2014]], [[2018 AFF Suzuki Cup|2018]]\n* [[Football at the 2011 Southeast Asian Games|2011 Southeast Asian Games&nbsp;\u2013 Football]]:\n::Gold Medal: 2011\n\n===Individuals===\n* Best Young Players: [[FAM Football Awards#Most Promising/Best Young Players|2010]]\n* Best Goalkeepers: [[FAM Football Awards##Goalkeepers|2010]], [[FAM Football Awards##Goalkeepers|2011]], [[FAM Football Awards##Goalkeepers|2012]], [[FAM Football Awards##Goalkeepers|2013]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.fam.org.my/news-articles/102-latest-news/583-senarai-pemenang-anugerah-bolasepak-kebangsaan-2013-100-plus-astro-arena-fam-football-award|title=SENARAI PEMENANG ANUGERAH BOLASEPAK KEBANGSAAN 2013 100 PLUS-ASTRO ARENA-FAM FOOTBALL AWARD|last=|first=|date=2 December 2013|website=Football Association of Malaysia.|publisher=Football Association of Malaysia|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129030449/http://www.fam.org.my/news-articles/102-latest-news/583-senarai-pemenang-anugerah-bolasepak-kebangsaan-2013-100-plus-astro-arena-fam-football-award|archive-date=29 November 2014|access-date=}}</ref> 2016\n*Goal.com Asian Under-23 Best XI for 2011<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/1717/editorial/2012/01/02/2825787/ji-dong-won-odil-ahmedov-hiroki-sakai-goalcoms-asian-under?ICID=AR_RA_1|title=Ji Dong-Won, Odil Ahmedov & Hiroki Sakai - Goal.com's Asian Under-23 Best XI for 2011|date=2 January 2012|website=Goal|publisher=Goal.com|language=en|access-date=24 June 2016}}</ref>\n*Goal.com readers' Asian Best XI of 2011<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sg.sports.yahoo.com/news/goal-com-readers-asian-best-xi-2011-javad-113000078--soccer.html|title=Goal.com readers' Asian Best XI of 2011: Javad Nekounam, Yuto Nagatomo & many more get the votes|last=|first=|date=10 January 2012|website=Yahoo Sports Singapore|publisher=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129122238/https://sg.sports.yahoo.com/news/goal-com-readers-asian-best-xi-2011-javad-113000078--soccer.html|archive-date=29 November 2014|access-date=}}</ref>\n*Goal.com readers' Asian Best Goalkeeper of 2011<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/1675/goalcom-polls/2012/01/03/2827965/who-should-be-the-asian-best-xi-goalkeeper-for-2011|title=Who should be the Asian Best XI goalkeeper for 2011?|date=3 January 2012|website=Goal|publisher=Goal.com|language=en|access-date=25 June 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Quotes==\nDon't  watch clock do what it does. Keep going, only you can change your life, no one can do it for you, and don't afraid to fail but be afraid not to try. Excuses don't get results so don't talk just act, show, and prove!!\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{NFT player|pid=40844}}\n* {{Soccerway|khairul-fahmi-che-mat/70066}}\n* [http://www.goal.com/en-my/people/malaysia/46630/khairul-fahmi-che-mat Khairul Fahmi Che Mat] at Goal\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{S-sports}}\n{{Succession box\n| before=[[G. Puaneswaran]]\n| title=[[Melaka United F.C.|Melaka United]] captain\n| years=2018\n| after=[[Shukor Adan]]\n}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Melaka United squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Khairul Fahmi Che Mat}}\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Malaysian people of Malay descent]]\n[[Category:People from Kelantan]]\n[[Category:Malaysian footballers]]\n[[Category:Malaysia international footballers]]\n[[Category:Kelantan FA players]]\n[[Category:Malaysia Super League players]]\n[[Category:People from Kota Bharu]]\n[[Category:Association football goalkeepers]]\n[[Category:Footballers at the 2010 Asian Games]]\n[[Category:Southeast Asian Games gold medalists for Malaysia]]\n[[Category:Southeast Asian Games medalists in football]]\n[[Category:Melaka United players]]\n[[Category:Competitors at the 2011 Southeast Asian Games]]\n[[Category:Asian Games competitors for Malaysia]]\n", "text_old": "{{Malay name|Khairul Fahmi|Che Mat}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2014}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Khairul Fahmi\n| image          =  https://www.google.com/url?sa=i&rct=j&q=&esrc=s&source=images&cd=&cad=rja&uact=8&ved=2ahUKEwi4saXruq7dAhXWdCsKHQ0ZAscQjRx6BAgBEAU&url=https%3A%2F%2Ffootball-tribe.com%2Fmalaysia%2F2018%2F03%2F26%2Fkhairul-fahmi-sedia-galas-tanggungjawab-menentang-lubnan%