mes|Football]]}} \n{{medal|Team|Malaysia}}\n{{Medal|Competition|[[Asean Football Championship]]}}\n{{medal|W|[[2010 AFF Suzuki Cup|AFF Suzuki Cup 2010]]|[[2010 AFF Suzuki Cup|2010]]}}               \n{{medal|RU|[[2014 AFF Championship|AFF Suzuki Cup 2014]]|[[2014 AFF Championship|2014]]}}\n{{medal|RU|[[2018 AFF Championship|AFF Suzuki Cup 2018]]|[[2018 AFF Championship|2018]]}}\n| club-update    = 22:30, 20 July 2019 (UTC)\n| nationalteam-update = 15:02, 23 March 2019 (UTC)\n}}\n'''Khairul Fahmi bin Che Mat''', [[Orders, decorations, and medals of Kelantan|'''P.B.''']]<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.sinarharian.com.my/edisi/kelantan/9-pemain-terima-pingat-sempena-hari-keputeraan-sultan-kelantan-1.102701 | title=9 pemain terima pingat sempena hari keputeraan Sultan Kelantan | publisher=[[Sinar Harian]] | date=11 November 2012 | accessdate=9 March 2017}}</ref> (born 7 January 1989 in [[Kota Bharu]], Kelantan) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for Malaysian club [[Melaka United]] and the [[Malaysia national football team|Malaysia national team]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sportsmalaysia.net/2010/10/23/100plus-fam-national-football-awards-2010-kunanlan-values-nomination/|title=100PLUS FAM National Football Awards 2010 - Kunanlan Values Nomination|last=|first=|date=23 October 2010|website=SportsMalaysia|publisher=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110322174006/http://www.sportsmalaysia.net/2010/10/23/100plus-fam-national-football-awards-2010-kunanlan-values-nomination/|archive-date=22 March 2011|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.malaysiansuperleague.com/team_info.asp?t=SL&tid=10|title=Super League 2012 Team Info & Players|last=|first=|date=|website=Malaysian Super League|publisher=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120515181251/http://www.malaysiansuperleague.com/team_info.asp?t=SL&tid=10|archive-date=15 May 2012|access-date=}}</ref> He is also a former member of [[Malaysia national under-23 football team|Malaysia U23]] and [[Malaysia national under-20 football team|Malaysia U20]] squad.\n\n==Club career==\n===Early career===\nAt his youth, Khairul Fahmi began his football career playing for the [[Kelantan FA President and Youth|Kelantan President's Cup]] team in 2006. He was the team's first choice goalkeeper for his side when they reached finals in the [[Malaysia President's Cup|2006\u201307 President Cup]] tournament. However, Kelantan later lost by [[Penalty kick|penalties]].\n\n===Harimau Muda===\nKhairul Fahmi was later chosen to be in the [[Harimau Muda]] team for the [[2007\u201308 Malaysia Premier League|2008 Malaysia Premier League]] season, alongside [[Ahmad Fakri Saarani|Fakri Saarani]]. Khairul Fahmi appeared in all 24 matches as Harimau Muda finished in 8th place.\n\n===PSV Eindhoven Youth team trials===\nKhairul Fahmi had also impressed the Dutch club, [[PSV Eindhoven]] and went for a-week trials with the club's Under-19 and Under-23 teams. He went there with his teammate, [[Mohd Asraruddin Putra Omar|Asraruddin Putra]] after they showed excellent performances in the [[2007 Champions Youth Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thestar.com.my/story.aspx?file=%252f2007%252f11%252f9%252fsports%252f19421884&sec=sports|title=Asraruddin and Khairul Fahmi to undergo trials with Eindhoven|date=9 November 2007|website=The Star Online|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131110161833/http://www.thestar.com.my/story.aspx?file=%2F2007%2F11%2F9%2Fsports%2F19421884&sec=sports|archivedate=10 November 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Return to Kelantan===\nIn 2009, Khairul Fahmi returned to Kelantan and registered for senior squad at the age of 20. He was the youngest goalkeeper ever to play for the Kelantan senior team. He made his appearances for senior squad after silly mistake from [[Syed Adney]] during their match against [[Kedah FA|Kedah]] in [[Malaysia Super League]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bolatoday.com/2010/01/kelantan-0-kedah-1-malaysia-super.html|title=Kelantan 0 Kedah 1 {{!}} Malaysia Super League 2010|last=JohnJenin|year=2010|website=Bola Today|access-date=24 June 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130118185028/http://www.bolatoday.com/2010/01/kelantan-0-kedah-1-malaysia-super.html|archivedate=18 January 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.stadiumastro.com/sukan/blog/blog-butiran/tenggelam-timbul-khairul-fahmi-che-mat/2024|title=Tenggelam timbul Khairul Fahmi Che Mat|first=Zainal Abidin |last=Rawop |date=17 March 2017|website=Stadium Astro}}</ref>\n\nIn 2010, he was part of the [[Kelantan FA|Kelantan's]] [[2010 Malaysia Cup]] winning team.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://malaysiadaily.info/press/Khairul-Fahmi-Che-Mat.html |title=Khairul Fahmi calm despite pressure |last= |first= |date=21 July 2011 |website=MalaysiaDaily.info |publisher= |access-date=6 December 2010 }}{{dead link|date=May 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> He also won The Best Young Player and Best Goalkeeper awards at the 2010 Anugerah Bola Sepak Kebangsaan 100Plus-FAM.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nst.com.my/nst/articles/Kelantancomeouttops/Article/|title=Kelantan come out tops|last=|first=|date=2 November 2010|website=New Straits Times|publisher=The New Straits Times Press (Malaysia) Berhad|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110629041301/http://www.nst.com.my/nst/articles/Kelantancomeouttops/Article/|archive-date=29 June 2011|access-date=6 December 2010}}</ref>\n\n===Melaka United===\nOn 7 May 2018, Khairul Fahmi signed a six-month contract with [[Melaka United]] until the end of the current season.<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.goal.com/en-my/news/melaka-united-secure-services-of-khairul-fahmi/qntcvpo3ng6s1qjfzy97ixz1h|title=Melaka United secure services of Khairul Fahmi|date=7 May 2018|accessdate=8 May 2018|publisher=Goal.com}}</ref> On 12 May 2018, Khairul Fahmi made his debut for Melaka United in a 0\u20130 draw against [[Perak TBG F.C.|Perak]].\n\n==International career==\n===Malaysia under-23 national team===\nKhairul Fahmi made his first appearance for [[Malaysia national under-23 football team|Malaysia under-23]] at the [[2010 Asian Games]]. He helped his team qualify into the second round but later lost to Iran, 1\u20133.<ref>[[Football at the 2010 Asian Games&nbsp;\u2013 Men's team squads#Malaysia|2010 Asian Games Football Squad, Malaysia]] retrieved 28 December 2010</ref> Khairul Fahmi became Malaysia's hero when he saved two penalties and they won 4\u20133 in the penalty shootout after a 1\u20131 draw against Indonesia to ensure Malaysia retained the prestigious SEA Games gold medal. Khairul Fahmi also helped his team qualify into the Men's Asian Qualifiers Preliminary Round 3 of [[2012 Summer Olympic|2012 Summer Olympics Qualification]]. However, Malaysia failed to win any matches in the group stage.\n\n===Malaysia senior national team===\nKhairul Fahmi made his debut against [[Oman national football team|Oman]] on 3 September 2010 replacing [[Sharbinee Allawee]] during the second half. He kept a clean sheet for the entire second half after Malaysia conceding 3 goals in the first half of the match.\n\nIn November 2010, Khairul Fahmi was called up to the [[Malaysia national football team|Malaysia national team]] by coach [[K. Rajagopal]] for the [[2010 AFF Suzuki Cup]]. Khairul kept a cleansheet against [[Thailand national football team|Thailand]] on a 0\u20130 draw. He also kept a cleansheet against [[Vietnam national football team|Vietnam]] twice in the semi finals. In the first leg of the finals, Khairul Fahmi played well against the Indonesians. The match ended a 3\u20130 win to Malaysia, thus earning another clean sheet to him.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.affsuzukicup.com/news/malaysia-3-indonesia-0-malaysian-blitz-buries-indonesia|title=Malaysia 3 Indonesia 0 - Malaysian blitz buries Indonesia|last=|first=|date=26 December 2010|website=AFF Suzuki Cup|publisher=WSG|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131109184410/http://www.affsuzukicup.com/news/malaysia-3-indonesia-0-malaysian-blitz-buries-indonesia|archive-date=9 November 2013|access-date=28 December 2010}}</ref> In the second leg of the finals held in Indonesia, Khairul Fahmi gave another outstanding performance by making numerous saves including a brilliant penalty save early in the match. The save proved to be a pivotal moment in the match in which Malaysia scored an away goal. Malaysia won on 4\u20132 aggregate and lifted the 2010 AFF Suzuki Cup title for the first time.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=/2010/12/30/nation/7704715&sec=nation |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101230234954/http://www.thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=%2F2010%2F12%2F30%2Fnation%2F7704715&sec=nation |url-status=dead |archive-date=30 December 2010 |title=Goalie makes it to global Twitter trending list |date=30 December 2010 |website=The Star Online |publisher=Star Publications (M) Bhd |access-date=30 December 2010 }}</ref> \n\nKhairul Fahmi was selected for the [[2012 AFF Suzuki Cup]]. On 26 November 2012, Malaysia's opening group match against Singapore ended up with the Malaysian side losing 0\u20133. The Lions scored the first goal through their captain, [[Shahril Ishak]] at the 32nd-minute. Six minutes later, Ishak once again scored a goal for the Lions as a result of Khairul Fahmi's blunder at goal. In the second half, veteran Singaporean forward [[Aleksandar \u0110uri\u0107]] completed the rout against the Tigers with the third and final goal of the game. The match resulted in [[2012 AFF Suzuki Cup]] holders Malaysia losing its first group match of the tournament, and Khairul Fahmi was subsequently dropped for the rest of the Tigers' campaign.\n\n==Career statistics==\n\n===Club===\n{{Updated|20 July 2019}}<ref name=\"K. Fahmi\">{{Cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/khairul-fahmi-che-mat/70066|title=Khairul Fahmi - Profil