tive in sports and has represented the school since primary school. On 28 December 2012, Khairul Fahmi married Nur Eilunie Natasha Jaafar.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.infoharian.com/foto-kahwin-khairul-fahmi-dan-leuniey.html|title=Gambar Kahwin Khairul Fahmi Apek Dan Leuniey|date=28 December 2012|website=InfoHarian|publisher=infoharian.com|language=Malay|access-date=24 June 2016}}</ref> They have a daughter named Kayla Elayna, and a son named Khaleel Emir.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mynewshub.my/myartis/?p=3378|title=Gambar Comel Anak Khairul Fahmi Dan Leuniey|date=10 February 2014|website=MyNewsHub.my|language=Malay|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140429045129/http://mynewshub.my/myartis/?p=3378|archive-date=29 April 2014|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n\n===Clubs===\n'''Kelantan'''\n* [[Malaysia Cup]] (2): [[2010 Malaysia Cup|2010]], [[2012 Malaysia Cup|2012]]\n* [[Piala Sumbangsih|Malaysia Charity Shield]] (1): 2011\n* [[Malaysia Super League]] (2): [[2011 Malaysia Super League|2011]], [[2012 Malaysia Super League|2012]]\n* [[Malaysia FA Cup]] (2): [[2012 Malaysia FA Cup|2012]], [[2013 Malaysia FA Cup|2013]] Runner-up [[2015 Malaysia FA Cup|2015]]\n\n===International===\n* [[AFF Suzuki Cup]]:\n::Winners: [[2010 AFF Suzuki Cup|2010]]\n::Runner Up: [[2014 AFF Suzuki Cup|2014]], [[2018 AFF Suzuki Cup|2018]]\n* [[Football at the 2011 Southeast Asian Games|2011 Southeast Asian Games&nbsp;\u2013 Football]]:\n::Gold Medal: 2011\n\n===Individuals===\n* Best Young Players: [[FAM Football Awards#Most Promising/Best Young Players|2010]]\n* Best Goalkeepers: [[FAM Football Awards##Goalkeepers|2010]], [[FAM Football Awards##Goalkeepers|2011]], [[FAM Football Awards##Goalkeepers|2012]], [[FAM Football Awards##Goalkeepers|2013]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.fam.org.my/news-articles/102-latest-news/583-senarai-pemenang-anugerah-bolasepak-kebangsaan-2013-100-plus-astro-arena-fam-football-award|title=SENARAI PEMENANG ANUGERAH BOLASEPAK KEBANGSAAN 2013 100 PLUS-AS